Install the VDO software packages, start the VDO services, and mark it for autostart on subsequent reboots Create a volume called vdo-vol1 of logical size 16GB on the /dev/sdc disk (the actual size of /dev/sdc is 4GB). 
List the volume and display its status information. Show the activation status of the compression and de-duplication features.


# dnf install vdo kmod-kvdo -y
# systemctl enable --now vdo 
# vdo create --name vdo-vol1 --vdoLogicalSize 16G --device /dev/sdc
# vdo list			=> vdo-vol1
# vdo status --name vdo-vol1 | egrep -i "compression|deduplication"
